00:13:45.110 --> 00:13:47.810 position:56%
So, Copland wrote the piece for
Martha Graham, it was premiered here

00:13:47.810 --> 00:13:51.720
at Library, it was a ballet, it
was written for 13 instruments,

00:13:51.720 --> 00:13:57.420
double string quartet plus base,
piano, flute, clarinet and bassoon.

00:13:57.420 --> 00:14:00.310 position:56%
The year after the ballet premiered,

00:14:00.310 --> 00:14:03.980
Copland made a sweet
out of it for orchestra.

00:14:03.980 --> 00:14:08.400
So, he took about 6 minutes out
of the "Simple Gifts" variation

00:14:08.400 --> 00:14:10.760
and if you go nips and
tucks here and there

00:14:10.760 --> 00:14:12.490 position:56%
and scored it up for full orchestra.

00:14:12.490 --> 00:14:15.650
And that's the way, I know
in my parents' generation,

00:14:15.650 --> 00:14:17.850
that's what everybody knew
at the orchestra suite.

00:14:17.850 --> 00:14:21.070
